{
  "texts": [
    "Each shapelet has a randomly selected length between predefined upper and lower limits.",
    "The quality of a shapelets is measured in the standard way with s Dist and information gain, and the best is selected.",
    "The data is split, and a tree is recursively built until a stopping condition is met.",
    "New samples are predicted by a majority vote on the tree's predictions and multiple trees are ensembled.",
    "The Multiple Representation Sequence Learner (MrSEQL) (Nguyen et al. 2019), is an ensemble classifier that extends previous adaptations of the SEQL classifier (Nguyen et al. 2017)."
  ]
}